 President Muhammadu Buhari has embarked on another trip for three weeks in London, the United Kingdom. Special Adviser, Media and Publicity to the President, Femi Adesina, who disclosed this in a statement said Buhari would return to the country after the vacation to commission some projects.  “At the end of the visit, President Buhari will be proceeding to his country home Daura where he will Commission developmental projects especially in the sector of education, healthcare and roads,” Buhari’s spokesperson, Femi Adesina, said. This marks the second vacation Buhari will embark on this year. Recall that Buhari has been seeing his doctors for undisclosed medical grounds since he assumed office in 2015.